cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.AI

This paper deals with speech segmentation and clustering, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a modification to DTW, which is a machine learning algorithm, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper uses clustering techniques, which can fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
